The paper deals with deep metric learning for image retrieval tasks, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel attention-based ensemble method, which involves training multiple neural networks, and optimizing them to attend to different parts of the object. This involves techniques from machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also evaluates its proposed method on standard benchmarks for image retrieval, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
